  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Anal fistulae are a difficult problem to treat. The optimal treatment for fistula involving
      the anal sphincter is unclear. Two standardly used methods of treatment are the ligation of
      intersphincteric fistula track (LIFT) procedure and the use of an anal fistula plug. The
      purpose of this study is to exam the rate of fistula closure between the LIFT procedure and
      the use of a fistula plug
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
